node.text:
Former President Pranab Mukherjee passes away at the age of 84 due to organ failures. He was admitted in Army Hospital (Research and Referral) Hospital in New Delhi. After undergoing brain surgery, former president developed a lung infection and slipped into a coma.
.
Pranab Mukherjee’s son, Abhijit Mukherjee confirmed the death news via Twitter. He quoted, ‘With a Heavy Heart, this is to inform you that my father Shri Pranab Mukherjee has just passed away in spite of the best efforts of Doctors of RR Hospital & prayers,duas & prarthanas from people throughout India! I thank all of You Folded hands’.

Written by - @p.s_2401
.

node.text:
People are being programmed into ignorance⁣
⁣
I don't know a single character on game of thrones but I can tell you what is in every single vaccine on the market off the top of my head. I've never seen an episode of the Kardashian's and have no clue what their names are but I'll you why 9/11 was inside job and how fluoride is destroying your brain. There is a growing and disturbing trend of overall ignorance in American culture. It’s the dismissal of logic, common sense and humanity and their replaced by entertainment, sedation, ignorance and deliberate gullibility.⁣
⁣
Rational thought is now the enemy. Critical thinking is the devil’s tool. The herd mentality has taken over, the anti-intellectuals become the metaphorical equivalent of an angry lynch mob when anyone either challenges one of the mob beliefs or says anything outside the mob’s self-limiting set of values. People accept without questioning, believe without weighing the choices and join the pack because in a culture where convenience rules, real individualism is too much work. Thinking takes too much time for most people…it gets in their way of trying to fit in.⁣
⁣
Being mindful and aware of what is really happening is both a blessing and a burden. It is frustrating to know that there is very little that is in my control but there is no way I would surrender to a life of conforming and ignorance, giving into the consumer culture that has been portrayed as the illusion of freedom when really, we are only creating more suffering for ourselves because we all know intuitively that materialism, drugs, alcohol, toxic pharmaceuticals etc…are temporary void fillers that keep us dis-empowered and vulnerable to the mental slavery they try to program into us.
